 Index Documents
You can add documents to Solr using various methods, such as through the admin interface, curl commands, or client libraries.

Add a sample document using curl:
 
 
curl http://localhost:8983/solr/mycore/update?commit=true -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '[
  {
    "id": "1",
    "title": "Solr Tutorial",
    "content": "This is an introduction to Apache Solr."
  },
  {
    "id": "2",
    "title": "Lucene Introduction",
    "content": "Lucene is a powerful search library written in Java."
  }
]'
